BRAZIL DAYBOOK: Vale SA Profit Surges, Brazil Investment Summit

-- B y   R o b i n   S t r i n g e r
-- 
2011-05-06T03:01:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-06/brazil-daybook-vale-sa-profit-surges-brazil-investment-summit.html
Vale SA, the world’s largest iron-ore
producer, said first-quarter profit rose to a record $6.83
billion as mineral prices and sales of metals such as copper and
nickel surged, according to a statement sent to  Brazil ´s
securities regulator yesterday after the markets close.  GOVERNMENT:
*President  Dilma Rousseff  has internal dispatches
*Finance Minister Guido Mantega leaves for Sao Paulo, where he
has internal meetings at Banco do Brasil
*Central bank president Alexandre Tombini has meetings in
Brasilia  WHAT TO WATCH:
*Brazil Investment Summit conference, with Itau’s Ilan Goldfajn,
Anbima’s Marcelo Giufrida and CIOs of companies, banks and
pension funds, takes place in Sao Paulo.
*Brazil’s CVM securities regulator and the U.S. SEC hold a news
conference on a week of meetings and training on supervising and
enforcing the  securities market . 9:30 a.m.  ECONOMY
*IBGE consumer price index IPCA at 9 a.m.
*Anfavea vehicle sales, production, exports at 10:30 a.m.  EARNINGS:
*Duratex (DTEX3 BZ)
*OGX (OGXP3 BZ), aft. mkt.  EQUITIES:
*Vale (VALE5 BZ) first-quarter profit rose to 11.3 billion reais
*Companhia Siderurgica Nacional (CSNA3 BZ) will pay 1.5 billion
reais in dividends  MARKETS
